.TH "gfs2_write_alloc_required" 9 "gfs2_write_alloc_required" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gfs2_write_alloc_required \- figure out if a write will require an allocation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gfs2_write_alloc_required
.BI "(struct gfs2_inode *ip "  ","
.BI "u64 offset "  ","
.BI "unsigned int len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ip" 12
the file being written to
.IP "offset" 12
the offset to write to
.IP "len" 12
the number of bytes being written
.SH "RETURN"
1 if an alloc is required, 0 otherwise
